   <styleUrl>#sev_severe</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in
Florida...

Little Manatee River At Wimauma at US 301 affecting Hillsborough
County.

* WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast.

* WHERE...Little Manatee River at Wimauma at US 301.

* WHEN...From Tuesday morning until further notice.

* IMPACTS...At 13.0 feet, The canoe rental area floods.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 9:00 AM EDT Monday the stage was 9.0 feet.
- Bankfull stage is 11.0 feet.
- Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage
tomorrow morning and continue rising to a crest of 12.7 feet
Wednesday morning.
- Flood stage is 11.0 feet.
- Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of
12.7 feet on 02/02/1972.
- https://www.weather.gov/safety/flood</Snippet>
