  <Placemark>
   <name>Flood Warning issued August 25 at 9:15AM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_severe</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>* WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast.

* WHERE...Savannah River near Clyo.

* WHEN...Until further notice.

* IMPACTS...At 11.0 feet, the back yards of several homes on Tom
Goethe Road flood.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 815 AM EDT Monday, the stage was 12.0 feet.
- Forecast...The river is expected to remain steady around 12
feet through the rest of the week.
- Flood stage is 11.0 feet.</Snippet>
