   <name>Flood Warning issued August 25 at 6:45AM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_severe</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in South
Dakota...

James River at Columbia affecting Brown County.

.For sites with a river forecast, the forecast includes
precipitation through the next 24 hours. Any future precipitation
could affect the forecasts.

* WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast.

* WHERE...James River at Columbia.

* WHEN...Until further notice.

* IMPACTS...At 15.0 feet, significant amounts of agricultural lands
are flooded.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 6:00 AM CDT Monday the stage was 14.9 feet.
- Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours
ending at 6:00 AM CDT Monday was 15.0 feet.
- Forecast...The river is expected to remain steady above flood
stage at 15.0 feet.
- Flood stage is 13.0 feet.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood</Snippet>
